BLUEBERRY FRENCH TOAST - is this what they call breakfast of champions or what?! Are team French toast or team pancakes?

By @carolinagelen 

Ingredients (3-4 servings)

Topping

2 cups blueberries 
1/4 cup sugar

French toast

2 eggs
1/2 cup heavy cream
1 teaspoon vanilla extract 
A pinch of salt
3-4 tablespoons sugar
6-8 slices of bread - brioche, challah, sourdough, etc. 

Butter for frying 

Powdered sugar and 8z or 250 grams whipped ricotta from my previous video for serving 

Instructions 

1. Combine the blueberries and 1/4 cup sugar and let them macerate until serving. 

2. Prepare the batter: whisk the eggs, cream, sugar, vanilla, and salt together. Dunk each slice of bread in the batter and let it soak as much of the liquid. 

3. Heat up a pan over medium heat, melt a knob of butter in the pan, then fry each slice of bread until golden brown on each side. 

4. Dust powdered sugar over the French toast, top with whipped ricotta and blueberries. 

Song: Pancakes by Jeff Kaale

FERMENTED CASHEW CHEESE! It’s really, really easy and you’ll need only 2 ingredients plus water and salt. 

Head to my blog and type ‘fermented’ in the search panel. It’ll be the first to pop up. 

I’m often asked how to serve cashew cheese. Honestly, it goes on anything. It makes a great dip (especially if you stir through chives or fill at the end), a toast or sandwich topper, stirred through puréed soups, tomato based pasta, or as a hummus replacement in a nourish bowl. 

It’s just an easy, delicious way yo add fermented food yo your diet, and a really introduction into fermenting your own foods.

By @panaceas_pantry

Here’s my hack to ripen avocados quicker. Bury unripe avocados in rice or place in a brown paper bag and store in a cool dark place like your pantry. Avocados produce ethylene gas, a plant hormone that triggers the ripening process. The rice or paper bag should trap the ethylene, holding it closer to the fruit and helping it ripen faster. Credit @myhealthydish

FERMENTED BLUEBERRY CHIA PUDDING. Really easy, really good GUT FOOD. By @panaceas_pantry 

Make sure to Save, Like, and Share 😘
 

Here’s the basic recipe:

1 cup frozen organic blueberries 
1 1/2 cups almond milk 
1/2 cup coconut yoghurt 
1/2 cup chia seeds

1. Blend together the berries and milk, then add to a large (very clean) glass jar along with chia seeds and yoghurt . It’s best in you use a jar with an airtight lid but it’s just not as easy to film 😆). Whisk together.

2. Ferment for approximately 12 hours, but note this can take longer. To asses when it’s ready look for all those bubbles (watch the reels again) and taste the pudding- it shouldn’t be sweet, and should be rangy and a bit fizzy.

3. Store in the fridge. To serve, top with whatever you fancy! I did raspberries, nut butter etc.

3 INGREDIENT MANGO SORBET 🥭 A healthier option instead of regular ice cream or sorbet 💛 Made with fruit, coconut and a little bit of maple, which you could skip if the mango is sweet enough. And this is peeerfect for these hot summer days! As a snack, breakfast or dessert.. YUM

By @fivesechealth 

- 2 cup frozen mango
- 1/4 cup coconut yogurt (4 tbsp)
- 2 tbsp maple syrup

Mix in a food processor until smooth. Let me know what you think 💛
